65
00:04:16,218 --> 00:04:17,854
I see.

66
00:04:23,991 --> 00:04:26,592
Did you choose a photo yet?

67
00:04:26,593 --> 00:04:30,619
Yes, a photo of the town.

68
00:04:30,619 --> 00:04:33,843
The results are in February, right?

69
00:04:33,843 --> 00:04:35,342
Yes.

70
00:04:39,217 --> 00:04:43,400
I didn't notice the tea olives fell.

71
00:04:50,664 --> 00:04:52,099
Yes.

72
00:04:55,539 --> 00:04:57,794
Our autumn of immaturity has ended,

73
00:04:57,794 --> 00:05:03,993
and a winter of judgment came to me and Kiyoi.

74
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,330
Oh no!

75
00:05:19,330 --> 00:05:22,058
Wake up! Kiyoi, wake up! Sorry, I turned off the alarm!

76
00:05:22,058 --> 00:05:24,454
Hey, wake up! Your shoot is today!

77
00:05:24,455 --> 00:05:25,855
No, it's too cold.

78
00:05:25,855 --> 00:05:28,760
Wake up!

79
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:31,361
Get ready. I'll take you to the station on my bike.

80
00:05:31,361 --> 00:05:36,400
It's fine, the agency will send a car.

81
00:05:38,163 --> 00:05:42,518
I told you last night that I have a late morning today.

82
00:05:44,602 --> 00:05:46,306
Oh, that's right.

83
00:05:47,241 --> 00:05:50,032
The agency's promising newcomer.

84
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:59,014
Kiyoi is rising up to stardom,

85
00:05:59,015 --> 00:06:03,471
so this creaky bike might not suit him anymore.

86
00:06:13,398 --> 00:06:15,196
Kiyoi-kun's cool today too.

87
00:06:15,197 --> 00:06:18,257
- Wow, eternal.
- Eternal.

88
00:06:18,257 --> 00:06:20,070
Eternal?

89
00:06:21,953 --> 00:06:23,834
When the Kiyoi Club makes a toast,

90
00:06:23,835 --> 00:06:28,740
we've decided to say "Eternal!" to represent our undying love for Kiyoi.

91
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:31,141
Undying love...

92
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:35,392
We pray for Kiyoi-kun's unending happiness.

93
00:06:36,476 --> 00:06:38,139
Eternal!

94
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:40,483
Eternal!

95
00:06:40,484 --> 00:06:42,186
Eternal.

96
00:06:42,187 --> 00:06:45,209
Excuse me, please lower your volume.

97
00:06:45,209 --> 00:06:47,081
I'm sorry.

98
00:06:47,812 --> 00:06:51,508
My feelings for Kiyoi will never die.

99
00:06:55,852 --> 00:06:57,030
Good morning.

100
00:06:57,031 --> 00:06:59,127
Oh, good morning.

101
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:01,727
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

102
00:07:01,727 --> 00:07:03,579
I got through!

103
00:07:05,844 --> 00:07:10,412
I got through the first round of Young Photo Graphica.

104
00:07:11,689 --> 00:07:13,659
Wait, you submitted?

105
00:07:13,659 --> 00:07:14,973
You should've told us.

106
00:07:14,973 --> 00:07:18,866
You know, I figured nothing ventured, nothing gained.

107
00:07:18,866 --> 00:07:21,670
You probably got your results too, Hira-san.

108
00:07:21,671 --> 00:07:23,906
Oh, right.

109
00:07:30,619 --> 00:07:34,378
[56th Youth Photo Graphica First Round Results]

110
00:07:38,273 --> 00:07:39,795
Hira?

111
00:07:39,795 --> 00:07:43,221
Wow, what a blank face.

112
00:07:43,221 --> 00:07:45,640
At least be a little happy.

113
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,339
I didn't pass.

114
00:07:49,367 --> 00:07:52,137
Really, I didn't pass.

115
00:07:52,137 --> 00:07:53,832
You're kidding.

116
00:07:54,546 --> 00:07:57,756
Why would they keep Sawazaki and not Hira-san?

117
00:07:57,756 --> 00:07:59,801
It makes sense.

118
00:07:59,801 --> 00:08:02,147
I had a feeling this would happen.

119
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,811
I'm gonna go then.

120
00:08:04,812 --> 00:08:10,860
But I was so embarrassed, I couldn't look up.

121
00:08:11,381 --> 00:08:13,866
I always spoke poorly of myself,

122
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:16,817
but I thought I had a knack for photography.

123
00:08:17,945 --> 00:08:21,548
It felt like they took a jab at my conceited self.

124
00:08:23,078 --> 00:08:24,562
Hira!

125
00:08:25,304 --> 00:08:27,042
Koyama.

126
00:08:30,866 --> 00:08:34,293
There is nothing good about me.

127
00:08:34,293 --> 00:08:36,401
No way.

128
00:08:36,401 --> 00:08:40,728
I couldn't congratulate Sawazaki.

129
00:08:41,937 --> 00:08:44,165
You were upset, right?

130
00:08:45,374 --> 00:08:50,057
Hey, about Noguchi Hiromi the photographer...

131
00:08:50,928 --> 00:08:52,046
Yeah.

132
00:08:52,047 --> 00:08:55,514
I think my brother can introduce you to him.

133
00:08:55,515 --> 00:08:58,148
He might look at your photo.

134
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,327
It's fine.

135
00:09:00,328 --> 00:09:01,896
Hira.

136
00:09:02,688 --> 00:09:07,173
What good would come from hearing why I didn't pass?

137
00:09:08,148 --> 00:09:09,678
Sorry.

138
00:09:12,226 --> 00:09:13,940
Bye then.

139
00:09:18,883 --> 00:09:20,835
Sorry.

140
00:09:20,835 --> 00:09:24,204
I know you meant well, Koyama.

141
00:09:24,204 --> 00:09:26,298
But it's no use.

142
00:09:27,506 --> 00:09:31,780
I tragically couldn't fulfill the King's mission.

143
00:09:31,781 --> 00:09:36,539
It reminds me of the cold winter air from high school.

144
00:09:36,539 --> 00:09:39,048
The winter I lost Kiyoi.

145
00:09:40,953 --> 00:09:42,978
The spring we met.

146
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:47,070
The summer of boundless energy.

147
00:09:49,908 --> 00:09:52,199
The calm autumn.

148
00:09:55,577 --> 00:10:00,415
But there is no winter between us.

149
00:10:00,415 --> 00:10:04,813
He disappeared along with the tea olives.

150
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,803
If I lost Kiyoi again,

151
00:10:08,804 --> 00:10:12,459
I'd never find a reason to live no matter how hard I search.

152
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:17,861
This happiness... How do I make this happiness last forever?

153
00:10:19,101 --> 00:10:24,768
Eternal!

154
00:10:24,768 --> 00:10:27,984
God, I don't have the answer.

155
00:10:27,984 --> 00:10:31,185
Eternal!

156
00:10:34,102 --> 00:10:35,820
I'm back.

157
00:10:37,616 --> 00:10:39,225
Welcome back.

158
00:10:39,226 --> 00:10:41,265
That's a big spread.

159
00:10:41,266 --> 00:10:44,618
Oh, is it?

160
00:10:44,618 --> 00:10:46,836
You made too much.

161
00:10:46,836 --> 00:10:48,518
It's normal.

162
00:10:48,518 --> 00:10:50,816
No, it isn't.

163
00:11:00,069 --> 00:11:02,275
- Okay, let's eat.
- They're out.

164
00:11:02,275 --> 00:11:05,706
The Young Photo Graphica results, right?

165
00:11:10,898 --> 00:11:13,959
- Hey.
- This is the chicken dish you liked.

166
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,805
The shrimp croquettes are fresh too.

167
00:11:15,806 --> 00:11:17,064
- The shrimp...
- No good?

168
00:11:17,064 --> 00:11:19,712
Um, I'll get a driver's license.

169
00:11:19,712 --> 00:11:21,389
I'll get a part-time job.

170
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:24,381
- So, um...
- It's fine.

171
00:11:24,382 --> 00:11:26,585
Just try again next time.

172
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:33,193
What? A-Are you not mad?

173
00:11:33,194 --> 00:11:35,311
Why would I be mad?

174
00:11:35,312 --> 00:11:37,466
I mean, I didn't meet your expectations.

175
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:39,892
You wanted me to win and become a pro.

176
00:11:39,892 --> 00:11:42,373
I never said to do it in one try.

177
00:11:42,374 --> 00:11:46,743
And who do you think you are, expecting to never fail? Are you a god?

178
00:11:46,743 --> 00:11:49,475
That's not it, but...

179
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:52,186
Then change your mindset and try again.

180
00:11:52,187 --> 00:11:56,960
I didn't win my first competition either.

181
00:11:58,342 --> 00:12:01,661
There are a lot of photo contests.

182
00:12:01,661 --> 00:12:06,607
You'll lose steam if you don't keep going, so keep sending them in.

183
00:12:06,607 --> 00:12:08,389
But...

184
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:11,112
Don't psyche yourself out.

185
00:12:11,112 --> 00:12:14,756
Well, I know that.

186
00:12:14,757 --> 00:12:16,390
How's this one?

187
00:12:16,390 --> 00:12:17,824
Look.

188
00:12:18,602 --> 00:12:22,032
The Ihei Nomura Photo Contest?

189
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:25,664
They say it's a photographer's gateway to success.

190
00:12:26,219 --> 00:12:29,029
I can't, I can't, I can't, I can't.

191
00:12:29,029 --> 00:12:31,776
- I can't, I can't, I can't—
- There you go again.

192
00:12:31,776 --> 00:12:36,483
But that's one of the most prestigious photography awards out there.

193
00:12:36,484 --> 00:12:39,343
They don't allow public submissions.

194
00:12:40,171 --> 00:12:42,445
It's for people with some level of experience.

195
00:12:42,445 --> 00:12:44,683
People in the industry take a survey

196
00:12:44,683 --> 00:12:47,764
on photos published from that year as candidates.

197
00:12:47,765 --> 00:12:49,664
Then a board selects the winner.

198
00:12:49,664 --> 00:12:52,431
- Then get chosen.
- Me?

199
00:12:52,431 --> 00:12:54,264
Yeah.

200
00:12:54,265 --> 00:12:57,874
Well, awards aren't everything, though.

201
00:12:58,982 --> 00:13:00,839
Thanks for the food.

202
00:13:02,906 --> 00:13:07,218
Once again, I was moved by the King's disposition.

203
00:13:07,218 --> 00:13:10,429
The shrimp croquettes are amazing.

204
00:13:11,193 --> 00:13:14,418
Oh, I'm glad to hear it.

205
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:18,856
Even though I failed, he didn't intimidate me.

206
00:13:18,856 --> 00:13:24,303
How do I set my eyes on such heights like he does?

207
00:13:25,281 --> 00:13:26,949
Here, too.

208
00:13:26,949 --> 00:13:28,841
Got it.

209
00:13:28,841 --> 00:13:32,614
No, there's no point in thinking about it.

210
00:13:32,615 --> 00:13:37,202
I just have to do whatever I can within my means.

211
00:13:38,263 --> 00:13:42,842
This little chestnut will create a future with Kiyoi.

212
00:13:42,843 --> 00:13:45,402
This little chestnut...

213
00:13:45,402 --> 00:13:47,948
will be the foundation of eternity.

214
00:14:06,263 --> 00:14:08,213
Eternal.

215
00:14:10,414 --> 00:14:14,061
Hey, why did you take the night shift?

216
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,421
Don't go collapsing on me.

217
00:14:21,842 --> 00:14:23,508
Thanks.

218
00:14:26,162 --> 00:14:27,233
You're kidding!

219
00:14:27,234 --> 00:14:29,113
What happened?

220
00:14:29,114 --> 00:14:31,693
Oh, um, K... Kiyoi.

221
00:14:31,693 --> 00:14:33,637
Can you go out for a little bit?

222
00:14:33,638 --> 00:14:35,355
Huh? Why all of a sudden?

223
00:14:35,355 --> 00:14:38,521
- Naho-chan is coming.
- Naho-chan? Who's that?

224
00:14:38,521 --> 00:14:42,144
Naho-chan is my cousin and used to live here with my grandpa...

225
00:14:42,144 --> 00:14:44,713
So for now...

226
00:14:47,020 --> 00:14:51,380
Come on, hurry up, Kiyoi, um...

227
00:14:52,170 --> 00:14:55,042
- Why are you so flustered?
- Over here.

228
00:14:55,763 --> 00:14:58,842
Kazuki!

229
00:15:00,625 --> 00:15:02,303
Is that Naho-chan?

230
00:15:02,304 --> 00:15:05,631
Sorry, I happened to be in the area.

231
00:15:05,632 --> 00:15:07,118
No, it's fine.

232
00:15:07,118 --> 00:15:10,910
Auntie told me to come check in on you too.

233
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,334
Oh, my mom?

234
00:15:12,335 --> 00:15:15,696
It's been crazy lately.

235
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:20,777
Your husband's busy with work, right?

236
00:15:25,015 --> 00:15:27,358
Naho-chan?

237
00:15:27,359 --> 00:15:29,280
Let's not talk about me.

238
00:15:29,281 --> 00:15:30,865
I was surprised.

239
00:15:30,866 --> 00:15:33,956
Isn't that guy in TV drama?

240
00:15:33,957 --> 00:15:36,840
The drama with Anna.

241
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,148
Oh, yeah.

242
00:15:39,148 --> 00:15:41,389
I was surprised by how attractive he is.

243
00:15:41,389 --> 00:15:43,648
He's attractive even up close.

244
00:15:43,648 --> 00:15:45,973
And he has an aura.

245
00:15:45,973 --> 00:15:48,515
Yeah, Kiyoi really is amazing.

246
00:15:48,515 --> 00:15:53,165
He was a model in high school, and his agency sees potential in him,

247
00:15:53,165 --> 00:15:54,780
so they're focusing on him a lot.

248
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:56,240
Oh, and look at this.

249
00:15:57,046 --> 00:15:59,569
He's making a guest appearance on Starlight Cafe,

250
00:15:59,569 --> 00:16:02,518
