251
00:16:02,518 --> 00:16:06,000
When you get the CD, it comes with autographed trading cards,

252
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,468
of which there are three types.

253
00:16:07,468 --> 00:16:12,311
I can't bring myself to choose, so I think I'm going to have to try hard for a complete set.

254
00:16:12,311 --> 00:16:14,676
Oh, and, um...

255
00:16:15,819 --> 00:16:17,492
And...

256
00:16:17,492 --> 00:16:19,390
You're more like a fan of his

257
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:21,820
than a friend, huh?

258
00:16:23,095 --> 00:16:25,403
Yeah.

259
00:16:25,403 --> 00:16:28,042
I guess I'm a fan.

260
00:16:28,042 --> 00:16:31,661
You're a fan and a friend, right?

261
00:16:33,805 --> 00:16:35,218
Oh, um...

262
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:38,561
I guess so.

263
00:16:38,561 --> 00:16:42,491
He's... a friend.

264
00:16:48,115 --> 00:16:49,822
A friend.

265
00:16:52,171 --> 00:16:54,032
A friend.

266
00:16:58,992 --> 00:17:01,647
Kiyoi doesn't eat cake, right?

267
00:17:08,732 --> 00:17:10,346
Watch it.

268
00:17:12,771 --> 00:17:14,502
Hey, Kiyoi.

269
00:17:14,502 --> 00:17:16,585
Watch your manners.

270
00:17:17,093 --> 00:17:20,143
Are you friends with Kazu-kun?

271
00:17:38,615 --> 00:17:41,719
Let's clean up quickly and have dinner.

272
00:17:43,146 --> 00:17:45,197
What did you talk about?

273
00:17:45,890 --> 00:17:50,500
It seems my mom asked her to come to check up on me.

274
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:53,955
- Seriously?
- Oh, but it's okay.

275
00:17:53,955 --> 00:17:57,615
I didn't tell her you're living with me.

276
00:17:57,615 --> 00:18:01,092
Then how did you explain why I'm here?

277
00:18:03,235 --> 00:18:06,600
Oh, I got a bit excited,

278
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:09,017
and she asked if I was a fan at first.

279
00:18:09,017 --> 00:18:11,717
- What?
- But...

280
00:18:11,717 --> 00:18:15,560
I was able to convince her that we were friends.

281
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:17,137
Okay...

282
00:18:19,337 --> 00:18:23,355
So I told her we're friends,

283
00:18:27,594 --> 00:18:30,400
but I actually...

284
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:33,000
Didn't like that.

285
00:18:34,716 --> 00:18:36,510
Hira...

286
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:39,195
You and I being friends?

287
00:18:39,195 --> 00:18:42,244
That's so disrespectful.

288
00:18:49,052 --> 00:18:50,785
Kiyoi?

289
00:18:52,064 --> 00:18:54,824
No, okay then.

290
00:18:54,824 --> 00:18:56,433
That's good then.

291
00:18:56,433 --> 00:19:00,100
Your mom must be relieved to know

292
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,940
you have a friend.

293
00:19:02,998 --> 00:19:05,552
Oh, sorry.

294
00:19:05,552 --> 00:19:09,456
Are you worried about my parents?

295
00:19:09,456 --> 00:19:11,601
Of course I am.

296
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:15,654
They're your parents, after all.

297
00:19:18,722 --> 00:19:20,913
It's fine, Kiyoi.

298
00:19:21,586 --> 00:19:25,350
You and my parents are totally unrelated.

299
00:19:26,202 --> 00:19:29,032
Unrelated?

300
00:19:29,032 --> 00:19:30,970
Yeah.

301
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:34,520
You'll never have anything to do with my parents.

302
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:37,499
So you don't have to worry.

303
00:19:41,437 --> 00:19:43,485
Kiyoi?

304
00:19:43,485 --> 00:19:48,028
I'll never have anything to do with your parents?

305
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,983
Never. I promise.

306
00:19:53,881 --> 00:19:55,935
Kiyoi?

307
00:19:55,935 --> 00:19:59,194
Do you have any idea how I feel right now?

308
00:19:59,194 --> 00:20:00,592
I don't.

309
00:20:00,592 --> 00:20:02,647
Don't just answer.

310
00:20:02,647 --> 00:20:05,608
If you don't know, then think.

311
00:20:06,421 --> 00:20:08,039
I'm sorry.

312
00:20:08,039 --> 00:20:11,389
I don't want you to apologize.

313
00:20:11,389 --> 00:20:14,279
But you're angry.

314
00:20:14,279 --> 00:20:15,999
It's always like this!

315
00:20:15,999 --> 00:20:18,717
When I get angry, you automatically apologize.

316
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:21,795
But you don't really understand what I was trying to say!

317
00:20:21,795 --> 00:20:23,421
There's no way I understand!

318
00:20:23,421 --> 00:20:26,848
How can a stargazer tell what the star is thinking?

319
00:20:26,848 --> 00:20:28,834
Why are you in space all of a sudden?

320
00:20:28,834 --> 00:20:31,459
There is no cross-over between you and me.

321
00:20:31,459 --> 00:20:33,495
Different paths and dimensions.

322
00:20:33,495 --> 00:20:35,313
That's why stars shine so brightly.

323
00:20:35,313 --> 00:20:37,843
If I actually tried to understand,

324
00:20:37,843 --> 00:20:40,234
it would only drag the star down.

325
00:20:40,234 --> 00:20:43,163
So what I want to say,

326
00:20:43,163 --> 00:20:46,932
is basically that...

327
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,480
I don't...

328
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:54,350
want to understand you.

329
00:21:01,154 --> 00:21:02,811
Kiyoi?

330
00:21:14,349 --> 00:21:16,750
So in the end,

331
00:21:19,076 --> 00:21:22,679
you don't intend to move toward me, huh?

332
00:21:26,748 --> 00:21:29,460
Wait!

333
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:31,210
Why?

334
00:21:34,146 --> 00:21:36,461
Why? Why are you stopping me?

335
00:21:39,813 --> 00:21:42,853
B... Because...

336
00:21:44,343 --> 00:21:46,200
You prefer

337
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:49,570
a one-sided love, right?

338
00:21:51,327 --> 00:21:53,538
Then stay there.

339
00:21:55,281 --> 00:21:57,010
I'm sorry

340
00:21:58,940 --> 00:22:01,620
for falling in love with you.

341
00:22:20,881 --> 00:22:23,126
Why is that guy...

342
00:22:25,232 --> 00:22:31,062
Kiyoi and I will never be able to understand each other.

343
00:22:31,062 --> 00:22:33,230
It's a cycle of crossing paths,

344
00:22:33,230 --> 00:22:35,560
only to fall apart again.

345
00:22:38,749 --> 00:22:42,068
We can't stop time the way photos can.

346
00:22:43,289 --> 00:22:45,022
That's good.

347
00:22:46,677 --> 00:22:48,677
How can you be so popular?

348
00:22:49,697 --> 00:22:55,520
Kiyoi teaches me a lot of new emotions.

349
00:22:57,708 --> 00:23:00,343
Get the grand prize and become a pro.

350
00:23:00,343 --> 00:23:01,659
Stop wavering.

351
00:23:01,659 --> 00:23:03,374
Don't psyche yourself out.

352
00:23:03,374 --> 00:23:06,380
I look best when I'm

353
00:23:06,380 --> 00:23:08,270
in your photos.

354
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:10,950
I don't get it.

355
00:23:10,950 --> 00:23:13,300
What should I do?

356
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:16,921
I can't recognize my own sin out of ignorance.

357
00:23:18,507 --> 00:23:20,305
God, you should...

358
00:23:22,452 --> 00:23:26,367
just kill someone like me.

359
00:23:26,989 --> 00:23:29,997
[This drama is fiction]

360
00:23:30,491 --> 00:23:32,697
[Next Episode]
The pain of unrequited love tasted sweet.

361
00:23:32,697 --> 00:23:34,724
I have someone I cherish too.

362
00:23:34,724 --> 00:23:36,314
- Yoshida!
- Are you getting married?

363
00:23:36,314 --> 00:23:38,020
It seems Hiromi Noguchi is mad.

364
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:42,519
If you keep sulking like a kid, you'll never get closer to him.

365
00:23:42,519 --> 00:23:45,087
Graduation is coming up.
